The paper deals with a space filling curve, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithmic aspect of the paper, which provides a method for enumerating segments of a given length, suggests that it could also belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM) categories. The proof techniques used in the paper, such as the concept of face-connectedness, are also relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and complexity theory (cs.CC).
